        </div>

        <h2>Who should choose Buildertrend</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Custom homebuilders managing complex, high-value projects</li>
          <li>Contractors with established lead generation who need deeper project management</li>
          <li>Operations with large teams managing many concurrent projects</li>
          <li>Builders managing extensive owner selections across multiple projects</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="cta-box">
          <p><strong>When you're ready for the full suite — Buildertrend is the market leader in residential construction.</strong></p>
          <a href="https://www.buildertrend.com" rel="nofollow sponsored" class="btn btn-outline">Explore Buildertrend</a>
        </div>

        <h2>Can you use both?</h2>
        <p>Yes — some contractors use Houzz Pro for marketing and lead capture, then manage larger projects in Buildertrend once won. This is more expensive than either alone, but for contractors where lead generation from Houzz drives significant revenue, the cost can be justified.</p>

        <h2>The verdict</h2>
        <p>Houzz Pro wins when lead generation matters and project complexity is moderate. Buildertrend wins when you have a full pipeline and need the deepest project management tools money can buy at the residential scale. Neither is wrong — they serve different stages of business growth.</p>

